-- Italian Banks Trade Parts of Claim on Lehman Brothers
-- B y   L i n d a   S a n d l e r
-- 2012-02-02T22:42:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-02/italian-banks-trade-parts-of-claim-on-lehman-brothers-correct-.html
(Corrects story published Jan. 23 to show that Credito
Emiliano sold a partial claim on Lehman.)  Credito Emiliano SpA (CE)  sold part of a
$152.5 million claim on bankrupt  Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc. (LEHMQ) 
to Banca di Credito Cooperativo di Alba, according to a court
filing. The part it sold is equivalent to $1,457.44.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Linda Sandler in New York at 
 lsandler@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Pickering at 
 jpickering@bloomberg.net  